<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-379-770  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 379 770.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>3D  August 1990 n28 p33(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Ventura: going for gold? (Xerox's Ventura Gold desktop publishingpackage) (Software Review) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Long, Kathy.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Xerox's Ventura Gold for Windows desktop publishing software putstogether the basic features, Professional Extension and networkingfeatures of the original Ventura package into one product.andP;  Itsadvantages include the ability to run alongside other programs,copy between programs, handle more file formats, and copy stylesbetween style sheets.andP;  Its disadvantages include the reliance onWindows for installation, the inability to recognize some types offonts, the use of too many steps when printing to file or printer,and the limited ability to handle color.andP;  The cost of the packageis 795 pounds sterling, the same price as the original versionwith only the basic features.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Xerox Corp. (Products).andO;Ticker:    XRX.andO;Product:   Ventura Gold for Windows (Desktop publishing software).andO;Topic:     Software PackagesEvaluationDesktop Publishing.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>